# Newsletter Includes — Title Above Items

The **INCLUDES** bar sits under pricing. **INCLUDES** is a centred title on its own row above the inclusion icons/labels.

## Rules

- Stack layout: title on top, items below (`flex-direction: column` on `.nl-includes-bar`)
- Title text is `INCLUDES` (no trailing colon), centred
- Items may wrap onto a second row when every inclusion is present — do not truncate labels
- Keep type compact (~10–11px) and icons ~13px
- Disclaimer sits immediately under OTHER INFO / INCLUDES (`margin-top: 8px`), not with a large gap

## Bad

```css
.nl-includes-bar { flex-direction: row; } /* title inline left of items */
.nl-includes-items { flex-wrap: nowrap; } /* forces truncation when many items */
.nl-disclaimer { margin-top: 48px; }
```

## Good

```css
.nl-includes-bar { flex-direction: column; align-items: center; }
.nl-includes-label { width: 100%; text-align: center; }
.nl-includes-items { flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; }
.nl-disclaimer { margin-top: 8px; }
```
